**Abstract:**
A summary document from 1991 listing 53 bibliography entries and notes on key works consulted for the Chantilly project. References include works by de Lubac (on Scripture and tradition), Guelluy on Ockham, Van Steenberghen on 13th-century philosophy, and Bouillard on knowledge of God. Also lists xeroxed works by Dumont, Hayen, Persson, Motte, Chenu, and others on medieval theological method and the theology-philosophy relationship.

**AI Recommendation:** Essential bibliography and research guide for the Chantilly project; provides overview of key secondary sources consulted.

